
# Ansible allow keeping sensitive data such as password or key in encrypted files, rather than a plain text in your ansible playbooks.

### LIST OF ANSIBLE-VAULT COMMANDS ###

# create a new encrypted playbook 
ansible-vault create vault.yml

# edit the encrypted playbook 
ansible-vault edit vault.yml

# to change the password of encrypted playbook
ansible-vault rekey vault.yml

# to encrypted existing playbook 
ansible-vault encrypt vault.yml

# to decrypt existing playbook 
ansible-vault decrypt vault.yml

